4 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Definitions. As used in [sections 2 through 16 13], unless the context
5 clearly indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
6 (1) "Board" means the board of livestock established in 2-15-3102.
7 (2) "Cattle producer" means a person who owns cattle in their own name or is an owner or
8 beneficiary of a business entity or trust that owns cattle in the state.
9 (3) "Cattle seller" means a person or entity that sells cattle. The term includes a person,
10 partnership, association, corporation, cooperative, trust, joint tenancy, tenants in common, and all other
11 business units, devices, and arrangements entities.
12 (4) "Collecting person" means a person who is responsible for collecting and remitting a cattle
13 assessment pursuant to [section 12 10].
14 (5) "Committee" means the Montana cattle committee provided for in [section 1].
15 (6) "Department" means the department of livestock provided for in 2-15-3101.
16 (7) "Montana cattle" means any cattle that have been physically located inside the boundary of the
17 state for the past 30 days.
